{"relation":"dlktk/discussion","args":{"id":"fivij-zatad","title":"make programming fun again — rerun under 0.17.1","subject":"q:how must the agentic-coding process change so the human keeps skill and the software resists aging","created_by":"chazu"},"source":"chazu","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"folul-tusab","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"a charter with a review horizon is revised, not ossified — the same living-constraint discipline dlktk itself uses","author":"maintainer"},"source":"maintainer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"folon-tabis","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"a global charter ossifies into the outdated standard everyone games","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"folir-buhuz","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"per-team relativism recreates the principal-agent problem — local optima diverge from the org's interest","author":"adopter"},"source":"adopter","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"folav-muzug","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Each team picks its own ranking by context","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fokus-talut","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"An org-wide engineering charter sets the ranking; teams inherit it","author":"maintainer"},"source":"maintainer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fokos-tifir","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"issue","text":"Whose value ranking governs gate strictness — an org-wide charter or per-team choice?","author":"reframer"},"source":"reframer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fojuj-tigut","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Advisory gate — flags un-comprehended modules but never blocks the merge","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fojiv-momar","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Blocking gate — a load-bearing module cannot merge until a human explains it","author":"educator"},"source":"educator","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fojas-pipit","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"issue","text":"How strict should the comprehension gate be — blocking or advisory?","author":"reframer"},"source":"reframer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fohad-zagof","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"the second seat replaces ad-hoc review rather than adding to it — a reallocation, and only on the load-bearing minority","author":"architect"},"source":"architect","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fogug-ropuk","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"pairing doubles the theory-holding labor on the core: two seniors per load-bearing module is more than a real team sustains — who does the second seat's work, and what do they stop doing?","author":"adopter"},"source":"adopter","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fogoj-lugup","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"only load-bearing modules get a pair — a minority — so it scales where it matters","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fogil-tibim","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"two holders is bus factor 2, and one-seat rotation refreshes it before it decays","author":"adopter"},"source":"adopter","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fogan-bukul","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Paired theory-holdership: two current holders per load-bearing module, rotating one seat at a time through hand-implemented handoffs","author":"architect","drops":["single-owner accountability (SA_indiv): no lone owner to point at","read-everything breadth (SA_team): non-core modules get no assigned holder"]},"source":"architect","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fofur-mutov","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"read-everything does not scale; diffuse ownership means no one is accountable and the theory diffuses to nobody","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fofos-narig","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"single owner = bus factor 1; the owner leaves and the theory evaporates","author":"adopter"},"source":"adopter","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fofit-potil","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Team-wide shared theory — no single owner, everyone reads everything","author":"maintainer"},"source":"maintainer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fofib-mosuv","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Single theory-owner per module — one person accountable for its design integrity","author":"architect"},"source":"architect","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fofaf-mugij","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"issue","text":"Where does the load-bearing theory of a module live — in one owner or the whole team?","author":"reframer"},"source":"reframer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"foduj-nozat","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"hand-flown legs are the first ritual cut under deadline pressure; who protects the calendar, and what ships later because of it? unsustainable as a standing practice","author":"adopter"},"source":"adopter","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fodom-barot","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"tie retrieval to the module that just paged someone at 3am — it is debugging, not a game","author":"educator"},"source":"educator","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fodim-burak","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"quizzing is condescending and gets switched off within a week","author":"adopter"},"source":"adopter","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fodan-razan","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"churn×criticality is a small fraction of the volume — that is the whole point of scoping it","author":"maintainer"},"source":"maintainer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fobus-nanuv","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"targeted deep review still cannot keep pace with the raw volume agents generate","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fobov-zufil","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"the contracts are executable (types + boundary tests); drift is CI-visible, not prose that silently ages","author":"architect"},"source":"architect","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fobod-musim","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"contracts rot too — who keeps them current as agents churn the implementations beneath them?","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fobig-titiz","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"the gate binds only load-bearing modules, not generated glue — throughput impact is bounded","author":"educator"},"source":"educator","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fobak-nohoj","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"argument","text":"gates throttle throughput to human reading speed — the velocity gain evaporates","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fizuj-zilug","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Spaced retrieval: the agent quizzes the human on generated code, scheduled on real incidents not synthetic drills","author":"historian"},"source":"historian","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fizol-sifib","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Churn-scoped deep review: aim human comprehension effort at high-churn, high-criticality modules only","author":"maintainer"},"source":"maintainer","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fizim-golaf","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Hand-flown legs: schedule regular features built entirely by hand to arrest skill decay","author":"shipper"},"source":"shipper","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fizap-rotal","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Human-authored architecture contracts: humans own the interfaces and module boundaries; agents fill implementations","author":"architect"},"source":"architect","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fivup-kupur","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"position","text":"Comprehension gate: a load-bearing module cannot merge until a human can explain it unaided","author":"educator"},"source":"educator","valid_start":1783993149}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fivol-mipin","disc":"fivij-zatad","kind":"issue","text":"What changes to the agentic-coding loop keep the human skilled and the software young?","author":"reframer"},"source":"reframer","valid_start":1783993149}
